{"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"symbolKind":"struct","roleHeading":"Structure","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ThreadPoolRef","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ThreadPoolRef"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib13ThreadPoolRefV","title":"ThreadPoolRef","role":"symbol"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GThreadPool","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" struct represents a thread pool."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef"},"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef\/init(_:)-23tja","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef\/init(_:)-34spm","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef\/init(_:)-5mqz7","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef\/init(_:)-92aql","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef\/init(_:)-eq03","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef\/init(opaquePointer:)"],"title":"Initializers"},{"anchor":"Instance-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef\/ptr"],"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef\/new(full:userData:itemFreeFunc:maxThreads:exclusive:)"],"anchor":"Type-Methods","generated":true,"title":"Type Methods"},{"anchor":"Default-Implementations","title":"Default Implementations","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef\/PointerWrapper-Implementations","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef\/ThreadPoolProtocol-Implementations"]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/threadpoolref"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol"],"type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To"}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ThreadPoolRef","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A thread pool is useful when you wish to asynchronously fork out the execution of work","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and continue working in your own thread. If that will happen often, the overhead of starting","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and destroying a thread each time might be too high. In such cases reusing already started","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"threads seems like a good idea. And it indeed is, but implementing this can be tedious"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and error-prone."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Therefore GLib provides thread pools for your convenience. An added advantage is, that the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"threads can be shared between the different subsystems of your program, when they are using GLib."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To create a new thread pool, you use [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.new"},{"type":"text","text":"]."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It is destroyed by [method"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.free","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you want to execute a certain task within a thread pool, use [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.push","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To get the current number of running threads you call [method"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_num_threads","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"To get the number of still unprocessed tasks you call [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.unprocessed","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"To control the maximum number of threads for a thread pool, you use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_max_threads"},{"type":"text","text":"]. and [method"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.set_max_threads","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Finally you can control the number of unused threads, that are kept alive by GLib for future use.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The current number can be fetched with [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_num_unused_threads"},{"type":"text","text":"]."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The maximum number can be controlled by [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_max_unused_threads","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.set_max_unused_threads","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]. All currently unused threads"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can be stopped by calling [func"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.stop_unused_threads","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef","isActive":true},{"text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GThreadPool"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"text":" reference to an existing ","type":"text"},{"code":"GThreadPool","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GThreadPool"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","name":"Note"}]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/ThreadPoolRef/init(constPointer:)":{"fragments":[{"text":"init","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"T"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"text":"constPointer","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind